-- Atlantis Wins Grant to Test Ocean Turbine in Bay of Fundy
-- B y   L o u i s e   D o w n i n g
-- 2013-02-19T15:22:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-19/atlantis-wins-grant-to-test-ocean-turbine-in-bay-of-fundy.html
Atlantis Resources Corp., a London-
based ocean-turbine maker, won $5 million from the Canadian
government to build and install a machine at the Fundy Ocean
Research Centre for Energy test site in the Bay of Fundy.  Atlantis will work with Lockheed Martin Corp. and Irving
Shipbuilding Inc. to build, install and monitor the 1-megawatt
turbine, the company said today in an e-mailed statement. The
Bay of Fundy has a tidal surge measuring as much as 15 meters
(49 feet),the worldâ€™s highest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
